article.headline: North Texas 92, Louisiana-Lafayette 74
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- Tristan Thompson scored 24 points, including all 13 of his free throws, to lead North Texas to a 92-74 victory over Louisiana-Lafayette on Saturday night. Thompson also was a perfect 3-for-3 from 3-point range. Adam McCoy added 15 points off the bench and Eric Tramiel and Dominique Johnson each scored 10 points for North Texas (13-10, 6-6 Sun Belt). Chris Gradnigo led the Ragin' Cajuns (8-15, 5-7) with 15 points. Travis Bureau and Lamar Roberson each scored 11, while Courtney Wallace scored 10 points. North Texas led by as many as 39 points in the second half.
